igue&#x02019; in CHQC and &#x02018;physical&#x02019; and &#x02018;existential&#x02019; in McGill. The intervention group had significantly higher satisfaction with care than the control group (p&#x0003c;0.001).</p><table-wrap id="HEARTJNL2015308638TB4" orientation="portrait" position="float"><label>Table&#x000a0;4</label><caption><p>Secondary outcomes at O1 and O2</p></caption><table frame="hsides" rules="groups"><colgroup span="1"><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="left" span="1"/><col align="char" char=" " span="1"/><col align="char" char="." span="1"/><col align="char" char=" " span="1"/></colgroup><thead valign="bottom"><tr><th rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><th align="left" colspan="2" rowspan="1">Control (n=41)</th><th align="left" colspan="2" rowspan="1">Intervention (n=43)</th></tr><tr><th rowspan="1" colspan="1"/><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">O1</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">O2</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">O1</th><th align="left" rowspan="1" colspan="1">O2</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td colspan="5" rowspan="1">Palliative performance scale (%, SE)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Ambulation</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">79.6 (25.2)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">69.2 (33.4)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">82.2 (22.7)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">76.0 (28.4)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Activity</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">100.0 (0.0)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">100.0 (0.0)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">100.0 (0.0)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">100.0 (0.0)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Self-care</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">45.6 (44.1)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">30.8 (38.1)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">59.8 (42.7)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">40.5 (42.9)</td></tr><tr><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">&#x02003;Intake</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">90.0 (6.0)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">91.9 (5.2)</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1">91.